<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-591-724  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 591 724.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Business Week  July 9 1990 n3168 p53(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Journey to the center of a gusher. (Schlumberger Ltd.'s Maxis 500system well testing equipment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hager, Bruce.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Schlumberger Ltd's Maxis (multitask acquisition and imagingsystem) 500 system is a series of nine tools connected to anabove-ground unit for testing oil and gas wells.andP;  Each device isequipped with a powerful microprocessor and radiation, acousticand electric probing is used to produce graphic pictures of anarea up to 30 feet outside the borehole.andP;  The Maxis 500 devicesrelay information at five times the rate of standard equipment or500 kilobits per second.andP;  The increased speed produces clearertransmissions and a better readout.andP;  Schlumberger plans to replaceits Cyber System Units, introduced in 1975, with Maxis 500 units.andO;Competition may come from another well testing technology calledlogging-while-drilling.andP;  This technique, which is also used bySchlumberger, uses test instruments placed at the end of the drillpipe to provide readouts during the actual drilling.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Schlumberger Ltd. (products).andO;Product:   Schlumberger Maxis 500 (Computer system) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Oil IndustryComputerized TestingComputer SystemsMeasurement Techniques.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Testing a well. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>